(55,	'privacy',	'privacy_description',	'<h4><strong>1. Introduction</strong></h4><p>Welcome to www.slottomat.com (the “Website”). We respect your privacy, and we are committed to only collecting and using your personal data in compliance with applicable privacy laws and regulations, including the General Data Protection Regulation 2016/679. &nbsp;<br>This Privacy Policy informs you (hereinafter “User,” “You” or “Your”) of how we collect and process your personal data when you access our Website, who we share it with, how long we retain it for and your rights as a data subject. &nbsp;<br>The Website is owned and controlled by Affcool LTD a Company formed in accordance with the laws of Malta, with its registered business address at 152, Office No. 9, Triq in-Naxxar, San Gwann, SGN9030, Malta (hereinafter the “Company,” “We,” “Us,” or “Our”). &nbsp;<br>Please read this Privacy Policy carefully before proceeding to use our Website. Your continued use of our Website will be deemed as your acceptance of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with this Privacy Policy, please do not access our Website. &nbsp;</p><h4><strong>2. The Scope of this Privacy Policy</strong></h4><p>This Privacy Policy only applies to Users who access the Website located at www.slottomat.com. This Privacy Policy does not extend to your use of any other websites or services offered by any third-party.</p><h4><strong>3. Data controller</strong></h4><p>The Company is the data controller for all the personal data that we collect from you. You can contact us at:&nbsp;<br>Affcool LTD<br>152, Office No. 9<br>Triq in-Naxxar<br>SGN9030 San Gwann<br>Malta</p><h4><strong>4. Updates to this Privacy Policy&nbsp;</strong></h4><p>From time to time, we will amend this Privacy Policy to reflect our new privacy practices and commitment to compliance with local privacy laws and applicable EU directives and regulations. We will post the updated Privacy Policy on this page and notify you of such updates by changing the last updated date on the top. You should review this Privacy Policy regularly to ensure that you are familiar with any changes. You understand and accept that your continued use of the Website after the effective date of the update will be deemed as your tacit acceptance of our new Privacy Policy.</p><h4><strong>5. Definitions</strong></h4><p>The following words, wherever used in this Privacy Policy, shall have the meaning as defined in Article 4 of the General Data Protection Regulation 2016/679:&nbsp;</p><p><strong>“Data Controller”</strong> - means <i>“the natural or legal person, public authority, agency or other body which, alone or jointly with others, determines the purposes and means of the processing of personal data; where the purposes and means of such processing are determined by Union or Member State law, the controller or the specific criteria for its nomination may be provided for by Union or Member State law.”</i>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>“Personal Data”&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;- means “<i>Any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person; an identifiable natural person is one who can be identified, directly or indirectly, in particular by reference to an identifier such as a name, an identification number, location data, an online identifier or to one or more factors specific to the physical, physiological, genetic, mental, economic, cultural or social identity of that natural person</i>”.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>“Processing”&nbsp;</strong>- means “<i>Any operation or set of operations which is performed on personal data or on sets of personal data, whether or not by automated means, such as collection, recording, organisation, structuring, storage, adaptation or alteration, retrieval, consultation, use, disclosure by transmission, dissemination or otherwise making available, alignment or combination, restriction, erasure or destruction</i>”.</p><p><strong>“Processor”</strong> means <i>“a natural or legal person, public authority, agency or other body which processes personal data on behalf of the controller.”</i><br>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>6. Personal data we collect and process&nbsp;</strong></h4><p>Your personal data that we may collect during your use of the Website includes your:</p><ul><li><strong>First name;</strong></li><li><strong>Email address;</strong></li><li><strong>Location data;</strong></li><li><strong>IP address; and</strong></li><li><strong>User content</strong></li></ul><p>We use your personal data for the following purposes:</p><ul><li><strong>User Content</strong></li></ul><p>When you post any comments on the Website, we will process your first name and the content of your comment to make it accessible to other Website Users. Please note that your User Content on the Website will be publicly available to other Users. You are advised not to reveal any personal information in any of your User Content that you do not wish to be made publicly available.&nbsp;</p><p>Legal Basis of Processing<br>The legal basis of our processing is our legitimate interest as set out in Article 6(1)(f) of the GDPR.</p><p>Data Retention Duration<br>We may, but we are not obligated to, retain your User Content until such time that you specifically request us to remove it from our Website.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><strong>Support request:</strong></li></ul><p>When you send us any support requests/enquiries by contacting us via email at info@slottomat.com, We will collect your name, email address and the content of your message. We process this information to respond to your enquiries/requests and to correspond with you.<br><br>Legal Basis of Processing<br>The legal basis for our processing of this personal data is our legitimate interest as provided in Article 6(1)(f) of the GDPR.&nbsp;<br><br>Data Retention Duration<br>We retain the personal data associated with your enquiry/support request for a maximum period of six months from the date of last communication. We will remove all your support request data from our records after the lapse of the six month period unless we are required to keep this information on other lawful grounds.<br>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><strong>Location data:</strong></li></ul><p>When you use our Website, we may request you to allow us to identify your current location (“Location Data”). We use this location data to ensure that you are not in a jurisdiction where our Services are prohibited by law.<br><br>Legal Basis of Processing<br>The legal basis of our processing is our legitimate interest as set out in Article 6(1)(f) of the GDPR.<br><br>Data Retention Duration<br>We will retain your location data two years from the date of your last visit on our Website.<br>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><strong>Subscribtion data:</strong></li></ul><p>We enable users to subscribe to weekly/monthly newsletter on our Website. When you subscribe to our newsletter, we use your name and your email address to send you our newsletter and other promotional material.&nbsp;<br><br>Legal Basis of Processing<br>Our legal basis for processing this data is your consent as set out in Article 6(1)(a) of the General Data Protection Regulation, which you freely grant us when you opt-in to receive marketing material from us. You can easily withdraw your consent by clicking the unsubscribe button at the bottom of our marketing email. If you unsubscribe from our newsletter, we will immediately stop processing your personal data for our direct marketing purposes.<br><br>Data Retention Duration<br>We retain your subscription data for only as long as you are subscribed to our mailing list. We will immediately remove your data from our mailing list at the time you unsubscribe.<br>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong></li></ul><p>We make use of Google Analytics on our Website that collects your IP address. Google Analytics is a web analytics service offered by Google Inc that tracks and reports website traffic. Google uses the data collected to track and monitor the use of our Web